&lt;p&gt;That's the best way to learn about the init, fork, parent process, child process and the shell loop itself.
As a side-effect, I also setup and used &lt;a class="reference external" href="https://www.jetbrains.com/clion/"&gt;CLion&lt;/a&gt;  on my computer.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description><category>software</category><category>tutorial</category><guid>http://www.xtoinfinity.com/posts/stephen-brennan-tutorial-on-writing-a-shell.html</guid><pubDate>Sat, 31 Dec 2016 01:39:14 GMT</pubDate></item></channel></rss>